    "transliteration": "THE 30TH OF RAMADHAN\r\n\r\nFor the last day of Ramadan, Sayyid Ibn Tawus has mentioned a supplicatory prayer that begins with:\r\n\r\nALLAAHUMMA INNAKA ARHAMUR RAAHEMEEN.\r\n\r\nIn most cases, the recitation of the Holy Qur’an is accomplished on the thirtieth of Ramadan; therefore, it is highly advisable to read the supplicatory prayer No. 42 of al-Sahifah al-Kamilah al-Sajjadiyyah.\r\n\r\nIt is also optional to say the following brief supplicatory prayer that is reported by Shaykh al-Tusi from Imam Ali Ameer al-Momineen (a.s.):\r\n\r\nALLAAHUMMASH RAH BIL-QURAAANE SADREE, WAS TA'MIL BIL-QURAAANE BADANEE, WA NAWWIR BIL-QURAAANE BASAREE, WAT LIQ BIL-QURAAANE LESAANEE, WA A-I'NNEE A'LAYHE MAA ABQAYTANEE FA-INNAHU LAA HAWLA WA LAA QUWWATA ILLAA BEKA.\r\n\r\nIt is recommended, too, to say the following supplicatory prayer that is reported from Imam Ali Ameer al-Momineen (a.s.):\r\n\r\nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA IKHBAATAL MUKHBETEENA, WA IKHLAASAL MOOQENEENA, WA MORAAFAQATAL ABRAARE, WAS TEHQAAQA HAQAA-EQIL EEMAANE, WAL GHANEEMATA MIN KULLE BIRRIN, WAS SALAAMATA MIN KULLE ISMIN, WA WOJOOBA RAHMATEKA, WA A'ZAAA-EMA MAGHFERATEKA, WAL FAWZA BIL-JANNATE, WAN NAJAATA MENAN NAARE.", 
    "english": "THE 30TH OF RAMADHAN\r\n\r\nFor the last day of Ramadan, Sayyid Ibn Tawus has mentioned a supplicatory prayer that begins with:\r\n\r\nO Allah, verily You are the most Merciful of all those who show mercy...\r\n\r\nIn most cases, the recitation of the Holy Qur’an is accomplished on the thirtieth of Ramadan; therefore, it is highly advisable to read the supplicatory prayer No. 42 of al-Sahifah al-Kamilah al-Sajjadiyyah, which begins with the following statement:\r\n\r\nO Allah, You have helped me complete Your Book, which You sent down as a light...\r\n\r\nIt is also optional to say the following brief supplicatory prayer that is reported by Shaykh al-Tusi from Imam Ali Ameer al-Momineen (a.s.):\r\n\r\nO Allah, (please) expand my breast through the Qur'an,use my body for the Qur'an, enlighten my sight by the Qur'an, make my tongue eloquent by the Qur'an, and help me carry out its duty as long as You keep me alive, for there is neither power nor might save with You.\r\n\r\nIt is recommended, too, to say the following supplicatory prayer that is reported from Imam Ali Ameer al-Momineen (a.s.):\r\n\r\nO Allah, I beseech You for the humbleness of those who humble themselves before You, for the sincerity of those possessing certainty, for the companionship of the pious ones, for the worthiness of the truths of faith, for gaining a share of all pious deeds, for safety from all sins, for the merit of Your mercy, for the qualifications of winning Your forgiveness, for winning Paradise, and for salvation from Hellfire."
}